have n't really seen a change.'' <ORGANIZATION> Neiman-Marcus </ORGANIZATION> has developed a $ 1,200 pair of shoes called `` the stars and stripes shoe,'' a white satin silk pump covered with pave rhinestones in red, white and blue, configured in stars and stripes. <PERSON> Stockwell </PERSON> said only one pair had been sold, by a branch in <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>. Another inaugural special, also going begging, was a $ 47,000 eagle brooch encrusted with gems. `` This would be perfect for <PERSON> Barbara </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>,'' said <PERSON> Stockwell </PERSON>. `` It really would, because of the eagle, and although it's all precious jewels, it's an understated piece. She likes the understated type of jewelry and it's really elegant.'' Are you listening, Mr. President-elect?
