<HEAD>For Release Weekend Editions Jan. 14-15</HEAD>
<HEAD>UNDATED: financial options.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 Here are some commmodity price trends for the past week: Wheat, corn and soybean futures retreated while oats advanced marginally on the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION>. Wheat for delivery in March settled Friday at $ 4.41 a bushel compared with $ 4.48 -RCB- a week earlier; March corn fell to $ 2.88 \ a bushel from $ 2.89; March oats rose to $ 2.43 a bushel from $ 2.42 -RCB-; and January soybeans slipped to $ 8.03 -RCB- a bushel from $ 8.17 -RCB- Cattle futures advanced while pork futures retreated on the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. February live cattle rose to 74.45 cents a pound from 73.40 cents; January feeder cattle rallied to 84.90 cents a pound from 84.35 cents; February live hogs dropped to 45.50 cents a pound from 47.12 cents; and February frozen pork bellies fell to 42.65 cents a pound from 44.45 cents. Precious metals futures retreated on <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Commodity </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. February gold finished Friday at $ 403.50 a troy ounce, down from $ 408.10 a week earlier; March silver slipped to $ 5.975 a troy ounce from $ 6.075. Crude oil futures surged but refined products were mixed on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. February West Texas Intermediate crude oil rose to $ 18.48 a barrel from $ 17.55; January heating oil fell to 52.95 cents a gallon from 53.60 cents; and January unleaded gasoline rallied to 49.97 cents a gallon from 47.72 cents.
